Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[A total of 23 ill people from 10 states were added to this investigation since the last update on [27 Apr 2018]; one death was reported from California; and 3 more states have reported ill people: Kentucky, Massachusetts, and Utah.

Most deaths related to EHEC are linked to the central nervous system complications of hemolytic uremic syndrome (HUS). This large and growing outbreak is the largest in the USA since 2016 with a significant percentage of hospitalizations (51 percent) and HUS (11 percent). - Mod.LL

